The Center works closely with distinguished faculty at New York University and other educational  institutions to design courses which focus upon the evaluation of policy and  the designing of new policy options based upon evidence and logic. Many of the  courses focus on using modern theories of political economy to explore the  incentives created by different policies in various institutional arrangements. The Center works closely with distinguished faculty at New York University and other educational  institutions to design courses which focus upon the evaluation of policy and  the designing of new policy options based upon evidence and logic. Many of the  courses focus on using modern theories of political economy to explore the  incentives created by different policies in various institutional arrangements.
